#nycmodelsearch #nycmodels #blondmodel #blondemodel

I had a very interesting conversation about the modeling industry recently. We talked about how everything had changed. Models don’t have to fit the right size, right height, skin color, hair texture, or even look. Diversity shows us all different types of models. 

But I was surprised that I accepted it. A white tall blond model looking like from the 90s I’m ok about it. Sometimes I heard that I could be a supermodel if I had started modeling earlier. Or I was born earlier. 
It’s not true. I will not. Because of the man’s supremacy. You know what does mean.

 And when I see diverse models I’m not jealous. I have nothing to share or split with them. But I’m happy to see more different women and different beauties. Those outdated standards have been imposed by men for women. We understand our beauty and our power differently. And I am always happy to contribute to it. 

To see women's empowerment makes me happy. 

I know that the majority of my followers are men. Sorry guys. The woman's era is coming 🤎

Me for @instylegreece by @anastasiafursova @solovey_solovey @kruchinina.pro @jasonlinkow @modelsdot @wilhelminamodels

Why my skin is so flawless on set? Obviously, the makeup artist did a great job, but I had prepared for the shoot too. Moisture your skin before the shoot. This is key! 

I’ve tried recently V.Biome firming cream with probiotics and vitamins from @neogen_us 🤍 Looove it. The cream is rich and has peptides and antioxidants. It’s very important for people living in big cities with a high level of pollution.

Advertising for a plastic surgery clinic. No Photoshop or surgery has been involved 💁‍♀️

💥Anyway let’s talk about it. I’m sure that many women compared themselves to unrealistic standards and they felt losers. Why should not you compare yourself with anybody?

💎First of all, you don’t know their lifestyle. For example, I’m a professional model. I get paid to look good. That means that any gym or sports activity is always included in my daily routine. I’m blessed to have a fast metabolism but I still eat less than an average American person. And it’s just my nature. 
Some people are born to be bigger, some people are born skinny. And both are beautiful.

💎Second, the majority of you have 2 legs that can walk anywhere, 2 hands that can create, 2 eyes that can see the beauty around you, 2 ears that can hear music and a nose that can smell life. You are already blessed to have a perfectly functional body. Don’t harm it by getting 2 inches down. 

💎And third, you would not believe me but it’s always a person who is jealous to have a similar life like you have right now. Your life is someone’s dream. 

We are not just our bodies, but our bodies are a part of our life. 

By @fazillah.photo for amazing and talented @karanmehtamd

The Usual seems familiar. The Unusual seems scary. That’s why conventional beauty exists. It’s usual. A human eye can identify the usual as beautiful in a second. 

The advertising business used to be limited by a second of human attention especially bigboards especially on highways. They needed a conventional beauty for fast promotion.

And then social media changed the game. We have more time to see a beauty transformation, a before and after. And you have time to admire some unconventional beauty ( not my case lol). And I think it’s beautiful 🤍

#gifted_by_katesomerville 💛

When you don’t feel well, you take vitamin C. Your skin will be grateful if you do the same for it. Serums and creams with vitamin C are great for antioxidant protection, healing blemishes, and reducing hyperpigmentation. Those cute freckles that you have as a child are not the same after the age of 25. Pigments stretch a cell and it loses elasticity. So it’s crucial to lighten dark spots. And a cream with a high percentage of vitamin C really can help. I’m using @katesomervilleskincare cream with 30% of vitamin C. You can find it in @sephora. 

Attention ⚠️ don’t use it more than twice a week for normal/combination skin. And one a week for dry skin. Do a test first. Apply the cream locally on the spots.
